Enum Constant Detail

ERROR_INVALID_TOKEN

public static final AuthError.ERROR_TYPE ERROR_INVALID_TOKEN
AuthError.ERROR_CATEGORY.ACTION Server has indicated an issue with the token/code parameters that were sent. If this Error is seen trigger indication for the user to sign-in again

ERROR_INVALID_GRANT

public static final AuthError.ERROR_TYPE ERROR_INVALID_GRANT
AuthError.ERROR_CATEGORY.ACTION Server has indicated the client is not authorized to use the requested grant(s). Local Authorization is invalidated. If this Error is seen trigger indication for the user to authorize again

ERROR_INVALID_CLIENT

public static final AuthError.ERROR_TYPE ERROR_INVALID_CLIENT
AuthError.ERROR_CATEGORY.ACTION Server has indicated the client is invalid. If this Error is seen the developer should update their APIKey

ERROR_INVALID_SCOPE

public static final AuthError.ERROR_TYPE ERROR_INVALID_SCOPE
AuthError.ERROR_CATEGORY.ACTION Server has indicated the current authorization does not have the requested scope. If this Error is seen trigger indication for the user to authorize again.

ERROR_UNAUTHORIZED_CLIENT

public static final AuthError.ERROR_TYPE ERROR_UNAUTHORIZED_CLIENT
AuthError.ERROR_CATEGORY.ACTION Server has indicated The authenticated client is not authorized to use this authorization grant type.

ERROR_WEBVIEW_SSL

public static final AuthError.ERROR_TYPE ERROR_WEBVIEW_SSL
AuthError.ERROR_CATEGORY.ACTION Android OS is older than FROYO and an SSL error was seen on Sign-in. This means the WebView will not display this to the user so we want the info to propagate to the client
